{"title_page": "Anthony Sims", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|American artist}}\n\n{{Infobox artist\n| name = Anthony Sims\n| style = [[Abstract expressionism]], [[Cubism]], [[Dadaism]], and [[Neo-pop]]\n| birth_name = Robert Anthony Sims\n| nationality = [[Mexican-American]]\n| image = Self Portrait by Anthony Sims.jpg\n| caption = Sims in 2020.\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1998|10|11}}\n| known_for = [[Painting]] and [[photography]]\n| movement = [[Neo-Expressionism]]\n| alt = \n| website = https://asimsart.com\n}}\n\n'''Robert Anthony Sims''' (born October 11, 1998) is a [[Mexican Americans|Mexican-American]] fine artist and photographer from [[Memphis, Tennessee]]. Sims is known for his high-energy colors that display raw human expression.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Zambrano|first=Matthew|date=|year=2020|title=An artist like you: the life of Sims|url=https://www.lovechaosmagazine.com/winter-2019/an-artist-who-perseveres-the-story-of-a-sims|journal=Love & Chaos Magazine|volume=Winter 2019|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.memphiscurrent.com/product-page/memphis-current-issue-no-3|title=Memphis Current Issue No 3|last=|first=|date=|website=Memphis Current Magazine|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><br />\n\n== Career ==\nAnthony Sims had his first gallery show at [[Jack Robinson (photographer)|Jack Robinson]]'s gallery in Memphis.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Yarsinsky|first=Adam|url=https://downtown500.com/2019/08/15/letter-from-asims/|title=A String of Misfortune.|date=|work=Downtown 500|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Sims became a member of [[Steve Kaufman]]'s American Pop Art collection in [[New York City]] in October of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.americanpopartinc.com/a-sims.htm|title=Artist: Anthony Sims|last=Vachier|first=Diana|date=|website=American Pop Art Collective by Steve Kaufman|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Sims has also made contributions to [[hip hop]] by creating cover art for rappers [[Issa Gold]] in November 2019 and [[Yung Simmie]] in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.manufacturedstudios.com/post/artist-anthony-sims-joins-hiphop|title=Artist Anthony Sims joins hiphop.|date=|work=Manufactured Magazine|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Nuglife (Ft. Issa Gold) \u2013 Long Flights|url=https://genius.com/Nuglife-long-flights-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Nuglife (Ft. Yung Simmie) \u2013 No New Friends|url=https://genius.com/Nuglife-no-new-friends-lyrics|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> Sims photograph \"1980's Glam\" was published in [[Vogue Italia]]'s magazine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/en/photovogue/portfolio/?id=222084|title=Anthony Sims - Vogue Italia|last=|first=|date=|website=Vogue Italia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/en/photovogue/Portfolio/Archive?photographer=A.%20Sims&md_pageIndex=0&md_page=0&md_pid=2288844|title=Archive - PhotoVogue - Vogue|website=www.vogue.it|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><br />\n\n== Selected collections ==\n\n* [[Manufactured Museum of Digital Art]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmoda.org/collection-artist|title=Collection-Artist|website=MMoDA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*[[Meridian Museum of Art]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.meridianmuseum.org/|title=Meridian Museum Archive|last=|first=|date=|website=www.meridianmuseum.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><br />\n\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Anthony Sims}}\n*[https://www.asimsart.com Official website]\n*[https://www.americanpopartinc.com/a-sims-gallery.htm American Pop Art Collective gallery]\n\n<br />\n\n{{US-painter-stub}}\n\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:American artists]]\n[[Category:People from Memphis, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Artists from Mississippi]]\n[[Category:21st-century painters]]\n[[Category:21st-century American painters]]\n[[Category:Expressionist painters]]\n[[Category:Cubist artists]]\n\n__INDEX__\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|American artist}}\n\n{{Infobox artist\n| name = Anthony Sims\n| style = [[Abstract expressionism]], [[Cubism]], [[Dadaism]], and [[Neo-pop]]\n| birth_name = Robert Anthony Sims\n| nationality = [[Mexican-American]]\n| image = Self Portrait by Anthony Sims.jpg\n| caption = Sims in 2020.\n| birth_date = October 11, 1998\n| known_for = [[Painting]] and [[photography]]\n| movement = [[Neo-Expressionism]]\n| alt = \n| website = https://asimsart.com\n}}\n\n'''Robert Anthony Sims''' (born October 11, 1998) is a [[Mexican Americans|Mexican-American]] fine artist and photographer from [[Memphis, Tennessee]]. Sims is known for his high-energy colors that display raw human expression.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Zambrano|first=Matthew|date=|year=2020|title=An artist like you: the life of Sims|url=https://www.lovechaosmagazine.com/winter-2019/an-artist-who-perseveres-the-story-of-a-sims|journal=Love & Chaos Magazine|volume=Winter 2019|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.memphiscurrent.com/product-page/memphis-current-issue-no-3|title=Memphis Current Issue No 3|last=|first=|date=|website=Memphis Current Magazine|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><br />\n\n== Career ==\nAnthony Sims had his first gallery show at [[Jack Robinson (photographer)|Jack Robinson]]'s gallery in Memphis.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Yarsinsky|first=Adam|url=https://downtown500.com/2019/08/15/letter-from-asims/|title=A String of Misfortune.|date=|work=Downtown 500|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Sims became a member of [[Steve Kaufman]]'s American Pop Art collection in [[New York City]] in October of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https: